Students learn about anti-drug know-hows via VR (virtual reality) devices at an educational base in Xingye County, south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, Nov. 18, 2021. Local authorities on Thursday hosted a series of activities to raise anti-drug awareness among young people. (Xinhua/Cao Yiming)  Students learn about the harm of drug driving via a VR (virtual reality) device which simulates drug driving experience at an educational base in Xingye County, south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, Nov. 18, 2021. Local authorities on Thursday hosted a series of activities to raise anti-drug awareness among young people. (Xinhua/Cao Yiming)  Students learn about the harm, traits and varieties of drugs at an educational base in Xingye County, south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, Nov. 18, 2021. Local authorities on Thursday hosted a series of activities to raise anti-drug awareness among young people. (Xinhua/Cao Yiming)  A staff member explains anti-drug know-hows to students at an educational base in Xingye County, south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, Nov. 18, 2021. Local authorities on Thursday hosted a series of activities to raise anti-drug awareness among young people. (Xinhua/Cao Yiming)